  <h2>Both of my parents work at the University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign, so education has always been something that was emphasized and encouraged in my family. 
  
  I have a younger sister who loves to call me and chat but hates to be asked to do anything. Growing up with her taught me the importance of negiotations, mediations, teamwork, and when to stand your ground.
  
  My family also has a dog named Lucy, short for Lucifer. We've had her since she was a puppy, and she's taught me the value of patience. 
  
  My family has helped shape me into the person I am. They've encouraged me to aim high, and I wouldn't be here if they hadn't made me into the person that I am today.</div>
  
