<div class="par-centertext">
  <h2>The first book in the Raven Cycle series was one of the first books I read with the book club at my high school. It's a difficult to describe because, as my one friend likes to say, it doesn't have a plot, but two of the major themes of the series are friendship and identity. These themes felt particularly relevant as I was trying to find my footing in my new school.
  
  It was through this book and book club that I began the process of finding my voice and the friends I wanted to share things with. About four years later, I decided to do a reread and got my new friends into the book series as well. In fact, we all liked the books so much, that we ended up going to Massanutten, Virginia, where the books take place.</h2>    
