<!--like it or not, your schooling, formal and informal, has been another factor that has brought you to, orepared you for this moment. Lets think through these systems, expectations, and outcomes. And let's also think a little about futurity...where is this learning, formal and informal...this unconcealing, taking you?-->
    
    <div class="par-centertext">   
  <h2> I attended Catholic school from Kindergarten through Eighth Grade, which is exactly as terrible as you might imagine.
  I then attended public high school where I, arguably, learned how to be a normal human being.I also had some of the most formative teachers and experiences. It was because of my high school U.S. History teacher that I got into statistics. He was the coach for the baseball team and asked me to do some basic statistics for the Varsity team.
  
  That experience took me a little out of my comfort zone with a different kind of calculations, but it was an experience that I really enjoyed. It was because of my experience doing sports stats that I decided to take A.P. Statistics my senior year of high school. During that class I found what I felt had been missing from my math classes, real-world application. </h2>    
